# agent-skills — secrets contract
#
# Skills read API keys from environment variables, never from the skill file.
# Copy the lines you need into your real env file, kept OUTSIDE this repo:
#
#     ~/.config/agent-skills/.env   (chmod 600)
#
# Naming: each skill reads its own variable first and falls back to the shared
# provider key. Set the provider key once and most skills work. Set a per-skill
# override only to give that skill its own dedicated key (separate billing,
# rate limit, or revocation). Variable names are fixed; do not rename them.
# This example file is committed and must never contain a real key.

# --- Provider keys (shared default) ---

# OpenRouter (https://openrouter.ai/keys) — image-gateway and other model calls
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Perplexity (https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api) — current-info-search
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=

# AssemblyAI (https://www.assemblyai.com/app/account) — media-transcription
ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY=

# --- Per-skill overrides (optional) ---
# Uncomment and set only to give a skill its own dedicated key. If unset, the
# skill falls back to the matching provider key above.
# IMAGE_GATEWAY_API_KEY=
# CURRENT_INFO_SEARCH_API_KEY=
# MEDIA_TRANSCRIPTION_API_KEY=
